step1:npm init
step2:npm install express ejs
step3:npm i --save-dev nodemon dotenv(dev dependensies)

nodemon =>used to restart our server everytime we make changes

step4:make a .env file under your project directory
step5:make a .gitignore file
             -.env
             -node_modules

.env=>contain secret and sensitive information

step6:go to package.json file
      "scripts": {
      "devStart":"nodemon server.js"
      },

step7:make a server.js file
      =>npm run devStart

step8:make a directory views and make a file inside this
      -index.ejs
      -login.ejs
      -register.ejs

step9:npm i bcrypt && include this in server.js file (for password)

step10:npm i passport passport-local express-session express-flash
step11:make a file passport-config.js






